<text top="82" left="263" width="634" height="54" font="1">The Tragedy of the Commons</text>
<text top="147" left="747" width="447" height="34" font="2">Technology/Land held in common</text>
<text top="209" left="771" width="408" height="34" font="2">Businessmen/Herdsmen have </text>
<text top="245" left="800" width="342" height="34" font="2">incentive to expand herds</text>
<text top="306" left="738" width="473" height="34" font="2">Uses/Herds eventually outgrow the </text>
<text top="342" left="784" width="375" height="34" font="2">land’s ability to sustain them</text>
<text top="403" left="717" width="507" height="34" font="2">Technology unusable / Land collapses</text>
<text top="464" left="752" width="447" height="34" font="2">Is modern technology in a similar </text>
<text top="500" left="772" width="406" height="34" font="2">position with common Internet </text>
<text top="536" left="894" width="154" height="34" font="2">ownership?</text>
<text top="597" left="726" width="489" height="34" font="4"><i>Is a solution to privatise the Internet?</i></text>
</page>
