<text top="82" left="263" width="349" height="54" font="1">Discouragement</text>
<text top="149" left="238" width="239" height="34" font="2">• Caller Line ID?</text>
<text top="185" left="238" width="314" height="34" font="2">• Data Protection Act?</text>
<text top="221" left="238" width="295" height="34" font="2">• Non-Contact Lists?</text>
<text top="257" left="292" width="795" height="34" font="2">• In the UK the Telephone Preference Service and Mailing </text>
<text top="293" left="332" width="255" height="34" font="2">Preference Service</text>
<text top="349" left="238" width="795" height="34" font="2">Email spam blocking and filtering is done by email providers</text>
<text top="385" left="238" width="939" height="34" font="2">• Offers some sophisticated counters that rely on pattern matching to </text>
<text top="421" left="278" width="177" height="34" font="2">detect Spam </text>
<text top="457" left="238" width="785" height="34" font="2">• Like antivirus software, relies on the principle of sharing </text>
<text top="493" left="278" width="789" height="34" font="2">information in order to reduce the impact of Spam on users </text>
</page>
